An Act prohibiting the use of coal tar sealers.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 111 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by inserting after section 244 the following section:-
3 Section 245. Coal Tar Pavement Sealant Products.
4 (a) For the purposes of this section, the following words shall have the following
5 meanings:
6 “Coal tar”, a viscous substance obtained by the destructive distillation of coal and
7 containing levels of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons in excess of 10,000 milligrams per
8 kilogram. "Coal tar" includes, but is not limited to, refined coal tar, high temperature coal tar,
9 coal tar pitch and coal tar pitch volatiles.
10 “Coal tar sealant product”, a surface-applied sealant product that contains at least a 20
11 percent coal tar pitch and is for use on an asphalt or concrete surface, including a driveway or
12 parking area, and are a major source of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons in the environment.
1 of 2

13 (b) No person or entity shall apply, or permit the application on property he or she owns,
14 a coal tar sealant product on a driveway or parking area.
15 Any person or entity who violates this subsection shall be punished by a fine of not less
16 than $500 and, for a second or subsequent violation, by a fine of not less than $1000 or by
17 imprisonment in the house of correction for not more than 1 year.
18 SECTION 2. Section 1 shall take effect on January 1, 2026.
